quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,121,"Nor do they spend anything (in Allâh’s Cause) - small or great - nor cross a valley, but is written to their credit that Allâh may recompense them with the best of what they used to do (i.e. Allâh will reward their good deeds according to the reward of their best deeds which they did in the most perfect manner).{1}",footnotes:1:{9:121}
  9,122,"And it is not (proper) for the believers to go out to fight (Jihâd ) all together. Of every troop of them, a party only should go forth, that they (who are left behind) may get instructions in (Islâmic) religion, and that they may warn their people when they return to them, so that they may beware (of evil)."
  9,123,"O you who believe! Fight those of the disbelievers who are close to you, and let them find harshness in you; and know that Allâh is with those who are Al-Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2)."
  10,79,"And Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) said: "
  10,80,"And when the sorcerers came, Mûsâ (Moses) said to them: "
  10,81,"Then when they had cast down, Mûsâ (Moses) said: "
